<header>
    <h1>SAVETHEPLANET – DAO GOVERNANCE</h1>
    <p>The decentralized future of the project</p>
</header>

<section>
    <h2>What is DAO Governance?</h2>
    <p>
        SaveThePlanet (STP) is designed as a decentralized ecosystem where all major decisions 
        are made by the community through <span class="highlight">DAO voting</span>.
        Token holders are stakeholders who influence the direction of the project.
    </p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Voting Rights</h2>
    <p>STP holders can vote on:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Allocation of environmental project funds</li>
        <li>Partnership approvals</li>
        <li>Development roadmap adjustments</li>
        <li>New features and upgrades</li>
        <li>Changes to tokenomics</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Proposal System</h2>
    <p>A new proposal must include:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Clear description of the initiative</li>
        <li>Expected environmental impact</li>
        <li>Budget requirements</li>
        <li>Implementation timeline</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Proposals with <b>over 1% of total STP supply</b> automatically move to voting stage.</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Voting Mechanics</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Each vote is weighted by the amount of STP tokens held</li>
        <li>Voting sessions last from 48 to 168 hours</li>
        <li>Proposal passes with a minimum 51% majority</li>
        <li>All results are stored on-chain for full transparency</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Anti-Manipulation & Trust Measures</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>On-chain identity verification for proposal submitters</li>
        <li>Whale control for critical votes (max 20% influence)</li>
        <li>Audit logs and open results for review</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Long-Term Vision</h2>
    <p>
        The goal is to transform SaveThePlanet into a fully self-governed global environmental movement
        where transparency and community power drive real ecological change.
    </p>
</section>

<footer>
